@startuml mailbox-default-sla-override
title Mailbox Create, Default Mailbox, and SLA Override
hide footbox
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontSize 16
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  GroupBorderColor #111111
  GroupBackgroundColor #EEEEEE
}

actor "Workspace\nOwner/Admin" as Admin
participant "Mailbox UI" as UI
participant "Routes +\nValidation" as Routes
participant "Auth + Workspace\nGuards" as Guards
participant "Mailbox\nController" as Controller
participant "Mailbox\nService" as MailboxService
participant "Billing\nEnforcement" as Billing
participant "Mailbox\nModel" as MailboxModel
participant "Workspace\nModel" as WorkspaceModel
participant "SLA Policy\nModel/Service" as Sla

== 1. Create mailbox ==
Admin -> UI: Enter mailbox settings\nand optional slaPolicyId
UI -> Routes: POST /api/mailboxes
Routes -> Guards: auth, active member,\nowner/admin role
Routes -> Controller: validated mailbox body
Controller -> MailboxService: createMailbox(workspace, payload)

== 2. Validate workspace and permissions ==
MailboxService -> WorkspaceModel: find workspace
MailboxService -> Billing: assert mailbox write allowed
opt SLA override supplied
  MailboxService -> Billing: assert SLA feature allowed
  MailboxService -> Sla: find active same-workspace policy
end

== 3. Apply mailbox settings ==
MailboxService -> MailboxModel: create active mailbox\nwith resolved SLA policy or null
MailboxService -> MailboxModel: handle duplicate email/default conflicts

== 4. Set default mailbox ==
MailboxService -> MailboxService: ensureWorkspaceDefaultMailbox()
MailboxService -> MailboxModel: ensure exactly one default\nand keep it active
MailboxService -> WorkspaceModel: update workspace.defaultMailboxId
MailboxService --> UI: success.mailbox.created

== 5. Link SLA override ==
UI -> Routes: PATCH /api/mailboxes/:id\nor POST /:id/set-default
Routes -> Controller: validated update/action
Controller -> MailboxService: updateMailbox() or setDefaultMailbox()
MailboxService -> Sla: validate active SLA override\nwhen set
MailboxService -> WorkspaceModel: sync default pointer\nwhen set-default
MailboxService --> UI: updated mailbox or compact action response

@enduml
